folder: 112th Street (East) & Between Park and Lexington Avenues., Manhattan, NY
original_title: Manhattan: 112th Street (East) - Between Park and Lexington Avenues.
text: 118-122 East 112th Street, south side, between Park and Lexington Aves. No. 120 is a junk shop. May 15, 1917. Gift of E.M. Jenks.

131 East 112th Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Lexington Ave. Building shown is a frame structure.

July 6, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
